Task: What is the linux command to

1. To view what's written in a file.
    cat <file_name>


2. To change the access permissions of files.
    chmod  -rwx <file.name>

    r (read): 4
    w (write): 2
    x (execute): 1  


3. To check which commands you have run till now.
    history
  
4. To remove a directory/ Folder.
    rmdir  <directory_name>
    rm <file_name>

5. To create a fruits.txt file and to view the content.
    vim fruits.txt  (create a file with content to write)
    cat fruits.txt  ( view the content) 


6. Add content in devops.txt (One in each line) - Apple, Mango, Banana, Cherry, Kiwi, Orange, Guava.
    echo -e "Apple\nMango\nBanana\nCherry\nKiwi\nOrange\nGuava" > devops.txt


7. To Show only top three fruits from the file.
   head -n 3 <file_name>


8. To Show only bottom three fruits from the file.
   tail -n 3 <filename>


9. To create another file Colors.txt and to view the content.
   cat > Colors.txt
   cat Colors.txt
   
10. Add content in Colors.txt (One in each line) - Red, Pink, White, Black, Blue, Orange, Purple, Grey.

  echo -e " Red\nPink\nWhite\nBlack\nBlue\nOrange\nPurple\nGrey" > Colors.txt
  echo "Red" > Colors.txt echo "Pink" >> Colors.txt echo "White" >> Colors.txt echo "Black" >> Colors.txt echo "Blue" >> Colors.txt echo "Orange" >> Colors.txt echo "Purple" >> Colors.txt echo "Grey" >> Colors.txt 


11. To find the difference between fruits.txt and Colors.txt file.
    diff fruits.txt  Colors.txt
